git cheat sheet

GIT CHEAT SHEET (RStudio Terminal, macOS)

Basics
  pwd                         show current folder
  ls                          list files
  git --version               confirm git installed
  git status                  what changed, what is staged, what branch

Create or connect repo
  git init                    start git in current folder (creates .git)
  git remote -v               show remotes
  git remote add origin <URL> add GitHub remote
  git remote set-url origin <URL> change remote URL
  git branch -M main          rename current branch to main

Stage, commit, push
  git add .                   stage all changes
  git add <file>              stage one file
  git restore --staged <file> unstage file (keep edits)
  git commit -m "msg"         commit staged changes locally
  git log --oneline --decorate -n 10   recent commits
  git push -u origin main     push main first time
  git push                    push current branch after -u set

Pull, fetch
  git pull                    fetch + merge from remote
  git fetch                   download remote updates without merging
  git pull --rebase           fetch + rebase (linear history)

Branches
  git branch                  list local branches
  git branch -a               list local + remote branches
  git checkout -b <name>      create and switch to new branch
  git checkout <name>         switch branches
  git switch -c <name>        same as checkout -b (newer syntax)
  git merge <branch>          merge <branch> into current branch

Rebase (use on your own unshared commits)
  git rebase main             replay current branch commits onto main
  git rebase --continue       continue after fixing conflicts
  git rebase --abort          abort rebase and go back

Conflicts
  git status                  see conflicted files
  (edit files to resolve)
  git add <file>              mark resolved
  git commit                  finish merge (if merging)
  git rebase --continue       finish rebase (if rebasing)

Undo / safety
  git restore <file>          discard local uncommitted changes to file
  git restore .               discard all uncommitted changes (danger)
  git reset --soft HEAD~1     undo last commit, keep changes staged
  git reset --mixed HEAD~1    undo last commit, keep changes unstaged
  git reset --hard HEAD~1     undo last commit and discard changes (danger)
  git stash                   save uncommitted changes temporarily
  git stash pop               reapply stashed changes

First push of a new branch (for PR)
  git push -u origin <branch>

Force push (only if you rebased)
  git push --force-with-lease

Useful one liners
  git diff                    changes not staged
  git diff --staged           changes staged for commit

Suggested .gitignore for R projects
  .Rproj.user/
  .Rhistory
  .RData
  .Ruserdata
  .DS_Store